        "description": {
            "name": "description",
            "type": "java.lang.String",
            "value": "I use Zend_View_Helper_Navigation_Menu, this helper allows url's to be null, it then creates a span instead of a href.\r\n\r\nMy personal router, based on Zend_Controller_Router_Route_Abstract has a assemble method that gives back null for pages that do not have an url.\r\n\r\nNow the bug occures, the Zend_Controller_Router_Rewrite assemble method always appends the baseurl and a slash\r\n\r\nIt can be fixed as follows.\r\n\r\n{code:title=Zend_Controller_Router_Rewrite::assemble (Current code)|borderStyle=solid}\r\nif (!preg_match('|^[a-z]+:\/\/|', $url)) {\r\n    $url = rtrim($this->getFrontController()->getBaseUrl(), '\/') . '\/' . $url;\r\n}\r\n{code}\r\n\r\n{code:title=Zend_Controller_Router_Rewrite::assemble (Patch)|borderStyle=solid}\r\nif ($url !== null && !preg_match('|^[a-z]+:\/\/|', $url)) {\r\n    $url = rtrim($this->getFrontController()->getBaseUrl(), '\/') . '\/' . $url;\r\n}\r\n{code}\r\n\r\n\r\nIt took me quitte some time to find out where the \/ came from.\r\nI hope you can fix this for future releases, so other people do not have to find this needle in the haystack ;-)\r\n"
        },
